&lt;Sea Gold Oil Corp> said it has agreed to a private-placement financing of 400,000common shares of its unissued capital stock with GulfInternational Minerals Ltd &lt;GIM.V> at 50 cts per share to raise200,000 dlrs Canadian.    The company said one of the conditions of the placement wasthe granting of a first right of refusal to Gulf in the eventthat the company should choose to enter into a joint-ventureagreement on any of its mineral claims currently held in theSkyline area.       If Gulf should sell any of the 400,000 shares, the firstright of refusal will be null and void, the company said.    Proceeds will be used for the continued exploration anddevelopment of the Sea Gold's mining properties. Reuter&#3;